::Feline::

She stood up, but could hardly stand and leaned against a large tree.  Her 
leopard skin was starting to fall off.  Her arms and legs were bare metal.  
Her tail was barren of skin as well and her face looked like she had on an 
old cat mask instead of her normal skin.  She fell to her knees and cried. 
As soon as she hit the ground, the rest of her skin fell off her metalic 
body.  She was now all crome.  Her looked like a full figured, slender, 
crome plated feline female bot.  The pain was starting to subside but she 
was still in agony.  She lay on her side on the ground, in the old leopard 
skin that once covered her body.  She meowed quietly, pulling the fur over 
her body and curled up in her old pelt.
